{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/week","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-07-02T11:40:47.655Z","repo":"CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks","descriptionHTML":"<div>\n<g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"anchor\" fallback-src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/2693.png\">⚓</g-emoji> A curated list of awesome git hooks</div>","description":":anchor: A curated list of awesome git hooks","stargazerCount":686,"readmeItemsUpdatedTime":1605468394000},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://knpw.rs/blog/direnv-git-hooks\">Automatically Manage Git Hooks with Direnv</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-15T19:26:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rudikershaw/git-build-hook\">Git Build Hook Maven Plugin</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rudikershaw/git-build-hook\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">30</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":30,\"repo\":\"rudikershaw/git-build-hook\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Install Git hooks and config during a Maven build.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-11T19:08:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit\">pre-commit</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5901,\"repo\":\"pre-commit/pre-commit\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A framework for managing and maintaining multi-language pre-commit hooks.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-01T13:21:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>commit-msg</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/commit-msg-hooks/enforce-insert-issue-number.hook\">enforce-insert-issue-number</a> - Make sure user did not delete the ISSUE-[#] string that was generated by prepare-commit-msg/insert-issue-number.hook. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/python-icon.png\" alt=\"Python Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>post-checkout</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/post-checkout-hooks/delete-pyc-files.hook\">delete-pyc-files</a> - Delete all .pyc files every time a new branch is checked out. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/python-icon.png\" alt=\"Python Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>post-checkout</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/post-checkout-hooks/new-branch-alert.hook\">new-branch-alert</a> - Display a message when a new branch is checked out for the first time. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>post-update</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/post-update-hooks/update-server-info.hook\">update-server-info</a> - Prepare a packed repository for use over dumb transports (e.g. http). <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-commit</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-commit-hooks/format-code.hook\">format-code</a> - Run command to format code and re-add any files modified after formatting. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-commit</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-commit-hooks/search-term.hook\">search-term</a> - Fail commit if a specific term is found in the code. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-commit</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-commit-hooks/spell-check-md-files.hook\">spell-check-md-files</a> - Check files with .md extension for spelling errors. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-commit</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-commit-hooks/verify-name-and-email.hook\">verify-name-and-email</a> - Fail commit if user.name or user.email is incorrect. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>prepare-commit-msg</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/prepare-commit-msg-hooks/include-git-diff-name-status.hook\">include-git-diff-name-status</a> - Include the output of \"git diff --name-status -r\" into the message, just before the \"git status\" output. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>prepare-commit-msg</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/prepare-commit-msg-hooks/insert-issue-number.hook\">insert-issue-number</a> - Insert issue number to beginning of the commit message. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/python-icon.png\" alt=\"Python Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-push</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-push-hooks/prevent-bad-push.hook\">prevent-bad-push</a> - Prevent push of commits where the log message starts with \"WIP\" (work in progress). <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>pre-rebase</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/pre-rebase-hooks/prevent-rebase.hook\">prevent-rebase</a> - Prevent topic branches that are already merged to 'next' branch from getting rebased, because allowing it would result in rebasing already published history. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>query-watchman</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/query-watchman-hooks/fsmonitor-watchman.hook\">fsmonitor-watchman</a> - Output to stdout all files that have been modified since a given time. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/perl-icon.png\" alt=\"Perl Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Git Hook Scripts</h2><h3>update</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/blob/master/update-hooks/prevent-unannotated-tags.hook\">update</a> - Block unannotated tags from entering. <img width=\"14\" src=\"https://github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks/raw/master/bash-icon.png\" alt=\"Bash Icon\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-24T19:16:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Video Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&#x26;v=fMYv6-SZsSo&#x26;t=140s\">Git hooks and practical uses. Yes, even on Windows.</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-22T02:46:35.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CaptainHookPhp/captainhook\">CaptainHook</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/CaptainHookPhp/captainhook\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">519</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":519,\"repo\":\"CaptainHookPhp/captainhook\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Git hooks manager for PHP developers.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-20T16:02:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Quick Start</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Pick a hook, any hook! Try the \"verify-name-and-email\" one if you're not sure where to start.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-12T17:06:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Quick Start</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Navigate to your project's hooks folder (.git/hooks).</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-12T17:06:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Quick Start</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>You should see a list of files already in there. Create a new file called the exact commit type that you want to use (eg: \"commit-msg\", \"pre-rebase\", \"pre-commit\", etc). Do not give it an extension.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-12T17:06:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typicode/husky\">Husky</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/typicode/husky\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">22.7k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":22723,\"repo\":\"typicode/husky\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Manage git hooks with a nice user interface.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-09T19:35:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sds/overcommit\">Overcommit</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sds/overcommit\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3426,\"repo\":\"sds/overcommit\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A fully configurable and extendable git hook manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-09T19:35:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://git-scm.com/docs/githooks\">Git hooks documentation at git-scm.com</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2\">Git Pro book by Scott Chacon and Ben Straub</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sitepoint.com/introduction-git-hooks/\">An Introduction to Git Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.atlassian.com/ru/git/tutorials/git-hooks\">Atlassian Tutorial on Git Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.vojtechruzicka.com/githooks-husky/\">Easy git hooks with husky</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.javascriptjanuary.com/blog/git-hooked\" title=\"Git Hooked\">Git Hooked</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-git-hooks-to-automate-development-and-deployment-tasks\">How To Use Git Hooks To Automate Development and Deployment Tasks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/automate-your-workflow-with-git-hooks-fef5d9b2a58c\">Automate Your Workflow with Git Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@Sergeon/using-javascript-in-your-git-hooks-f0ce09477334\" title=\"Using JavaScript in Your Git Hooks\">Using JavaScript in Your Git Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/an-in-depth-look-at-git-hooks\">An In-Depth Look at Git Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Written Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.tygertec.com/git-hooks-practical-uses-windows/\">Git hooks and practical uses. Yes, even on Windows.</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Video Guides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aB3eq52sZSU\">Git Hooks Part 1 - Getting Started</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-27T15:39:40.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/vuejs/awesome-vue","repo":"vuejs/awesome-vue"},"next":null},"pageContext":{"type":"week","repo":"CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks","id":"awesomes/github.com/CompSciLauren/awesome-git-hooks","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/vuejs/awesome-vue","nextId":null}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2355899892","2744905544"]}